
[1]exaggeration

   EXAGGERA'TION, n. A heaping together; heap; accumulation.

   1. In rhetoric, amplification; a representation of things beyond the
   truth; hyperbolical representation, whether of good or evil.

   2. In painting, a method of giving a representation of things too
   strong for the life.
